{"FIMBRIA":[{"def":"A fringe, or fringed border.","pos":""}],"FIMBRIATE":[{"def":"Having the edge or extremity bordered by filiform processes thicker than hairs; fringed; as, the fimbriate petals of the pink; the fimbriate end of the Fallopian tube.","pos":""}],"FIMBRIATED":[{"def":"Having a very narrow border of another tincture; -- said esp.","pos":""}],"FIMBRICATE":[{"def":"fringed, on one side only, by long, straight hairs, as the antennæ of certain insects.","pos":""}]}